Cerner Analysis Project¶

Video Presentation Link¶

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pHw7H13BwWc

Purpose of Project¶

The goal of this project will be to compare the viewpoints of Cerner from reviews and social media. The hope is to gain a complete understanding of the company and how they operate, along with knowing weaknesses and how to try and improve upon them. The first section pertains to social media and Twitter, and the second section contains reviews from a medical software review website.

Business Questions¶

1) To provide descriptive analytics for Cerner to gain an understanding of topics the company finds itself around 2) To determine how Cerner is viewed from the public?3) Ways in which Cerner can improve in the form of customer service4) How they are viewed in the industry

1) Twitter Analysis¶

Convert to CSV¶

In [98]:
# More codes for extracting information from tweets

ids = [T['id_str'] for T in tweets]
times = [T['created_at'] for T in tweets]
texts = [T['text'] for T in tweets]
screen_names = [T['user']['screen_name'] for T in tweets]
lang = [T['user']['lang'] for T in tweets]
followers_count = [T['user']['followers_count'] for T in tweets]
friends_count = [T['user']['friends_count'] for T in tweets]
names = [T['user']['name'] for T in tweets]
lats = [(T['geo']['coordinates'][0] if T['geo'] else None) for T in tweets]
lons = [(T['geo']['coordinates'][1] if T['geo'] else None) for T in tweets]
place_names = [(T['place']['full_name'] if T['place'] else None) for T in tweets]
place_types = [(T['place']['place_type'] if T['place'] else None) for T in tweets]

# open an output csv file to write to
out = open('tweetdata.csv', 'w', encoding='UTF-8', newline='')

# write the header of our CSV as its first line
out.write('id,created at,text,screen name,lang,followers_count,friends_count,name,lat,lon,place name,place type\n')

# merge each individual list into a single list using the zip function
rows = list(zip(ids, times, texts, screen_names, lang, followers_count, friends_count, names, lats, lons, place_names, place_types))

# use the writer module on our csv file
csv = csv.writer(out)

# use one value from each of our rows list and write it to the csv as a new row
for row in rows:
    values = [value for value in row]
    #values = [(value.encode('utf8') if hasattr(value, 'encode') else value) for value in row]
    csv.writerow(values)

# close our csv file when done
out.close()

Twitter Analysis Summary¶

Analyzing the data comes to the conclusion that within social media Cerner is not looked at as a very positive company. The majority of tweets containing the word cerner are french, and this may be due to the word meaning "identify" in French. Out of the total data of 2291 tweets, only 463 are english. There was an average tweets per user of 1.03. Within the english data set 426 were retweets, while only 37 are original tweets. Also 444 tweets did not mention Cerner, while only 19 did. The company itself also only had 6 tweets with 1 hastag being Cerner. The 3 most popular hastags were ECF19, womenandmed, and womeninit. The sentiment for the english data set was an average of -.06, which indicates it has a slight negative overall sentiment. The lowest and highest sentiments in the data set are -.7 and .957 respectively. The total number of positive tweets are 23, nuetral are 113, and negative are 327.

# clean and tokenize
def text_processing(review):
    # what if you have additional stopwords to be removed
    tokens = str(review)
    #lowecases
    tokens = tokens.lower()
    # Remove useless numbers and alphanumerical words
    tokens = re.sub("[^a-zA-Z0-9]", " ", tokens)
    #tokenization or word split
    tokens = word_tokenize(tokens)
    #get stemming words or lemmas
    wordnet_lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
    tokens = (wordnet_lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in tokens)
    #additional stopwrods
    more_stopwords = set(('cant', 'aint', 'today'))
    extra_stoplist = set(stopwords.words('english')) | more_stopwords
    tokens = (word for word in tokens if word not in extra_stoplist)
    # Filter non-alphanumeric characters from tokens
    tokens = (word for word in tokens if word.isalpha())
    #remove short words
    tokens = (word for word in tokens if len(word) >= 3)
    return tokens

# append sentiment
positive_review = []
negative_review = []
neutral_review = []

for row in reviews:
    #tweet = row[0]
    score = TextBlob(row).sentiment.polarity
    if score > 0:
        positive_review.append(row)
    elif score == 0:
        neutral_review.append(row)
    else:
        negative_review.append(row)

Review Analysis Summary¶

This data set contains only 21 reviews. When analyzing the reviews the most popular words were: Patient, System, Software, cerner, time, information, use, powerchart, charting and easy. The most popular bigrams were cerner & powerchart, patient & chart, user & friendly, get& used, easy & navigate. When running textblob sentiment on the reviews the average polarity and subjectivity are .18 and .45 respectively. The mimimum for polarity and subjectivity are -.02 and 0 respectively. Where as the maximum is .43 and .86 respectively. The total number of positive reviews are 19, negative reviews are 1, and nuetral is 1. The most popular words in positive reviews are software, cerner, system, information, and patient. The most popular words in negative reviews are sometimes, difficult, navigate and notes.

Recommendations¶

1) Cerner is very popular amongst those who emphasize the fact of women in IT. This may be due to negative or positive sentiment, however they need to embrace this stance since it is often polarizing and can influence followers. 2) Cerner is viewed slightly negatively, with a sentiment score of -.06. This showcases that the public looks at Cerner very differently than those in the healthcare industry. To bridge this gap Cerner should engage in more promo's online and possibly try and convey to the public what they do that's positive. There was a total of 327 negative tweets, compared to 23 and 113 positive and nuetral tweets respectively. 3) The most popular negative words among reviews were difficult, navigate, and notes. So it seems that making the software easier to navigate would improve customer service among healthcare professional. 4) As previosuly mentioned, Cerner is looked at slightly negatively amongst the public.However among healthcare professionals who have written reviews, they are viewed very positively at .18. This showcases that the public looks at Cerner very differently than those in the healthcare industry. Within the industry the key words that describe them postively are software, cerner, system, information, and patient. This shows the customers understanding that cerner puts the system, information, patients, and software at the forefront of their operations. Only 1 review was negative.
